<item>
            <title>[SPARK-35672] Spark fails to launch executors with very large user classpath lists on YARN</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-35672</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When running Spark on YARN, the &lt;tt&gt;user-class-path&lt;/tt&gt; argument to &lt;tt&gt;CoarseGrainedExecutorBackend&lt;/tt&gt; is used to pass a list of user JAR URIs to executor processes. The argument is specified once for each JAR, and the URIs are fully-qualified, so the paths can be quite long. With large user JAR lists (say 1000+), this can result in system-level argument length limits being exceeded, typically manifesting as the error message:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
/bin/bash: Argument list too &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.google.com/search?q=spark%20%22%2Fbin%2Fbash%3A%20argument%20list%20too%20long%22&amp;amp;oq=spark%20%22%2Fbin%2Fbash%3A%20argument%20list%20too%20long%22&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Google search&lt;/a&gt; indicates that this is not a theoretical problem and afflicts real users, including ours. This issue was originally observed on Spark 2.3, but has been confirmed to exist in the master branch as well.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Linux RHEL7&lt;br/&gt;
Spark 3.1.1&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
